data.title: Prime Minister Narendra Modi congratulated the Indian cricket team after they won the T20 World Cup on Saturday. India defeated South...
data.meta_description:
1,551 likes, 145 comments - theprintindia on June 29, 2024: "Prime Minister Narendra Modi congratulated the Indian cricket team after they won the T20 World Cup on Saturday.

India defeated South Africa by seven runs and won the 2024 T20 World Cup at the Kensington Oval in Barbados.

"CHAMPIONS! Our team brings the T20 World Cup home in STYLE! We are proud of the Indian Cricket Team. This match was HISTORIC," PM said in a post on X, along with a video message for the team.

#pmmodi #indiateam #cricket #indiancricketteam #t20worldcup #2024t20worldcup #worldcup".
